-- U.S. Orange-Juice Sales May Decline 8.9% as Prices Increase, Florida Says
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   C a m p b e l l
-- 2010-10-20T17:37:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/u-s-orange-juice-sales-may-decline-8-9-as-prices-increase-florida-says.html
Orange-juice sales by U.S. retailers
may fall as much as 8.9 percent in the 2010-2011 season, the
Florida Department of Citrus said.  Sales may be 552 million gallons to 586.1 million gallons,
down from the estimated 605.7 million gallons in the 2009-2010
season, the agency said today in a report, citing Nielsen Co.
data.  Retail prices may range from $5.57 to $5.91 a gallon in the
2010-2011 season, up from an estimated $5.51 in the 2009-2010
season, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elizabeth Campbell in New York at 
 ecampbell14@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
